dataIdInfo.idPurp: Individual line segments along the overall boundary of recorded subdivision maps in San Diego County
dataIdInfo.idAbs: Line features of SUBDIVISION layer. Individual line segments along the overall boundary of recorded subdivision maps in San Diego County. Line segments are used in creation of SUBDIVISION layer polygons and indicate type of boundary line for each segment.Layer does not show all subdivision maps recorded in the County.

Consts.useLimit: Data is generalized and created for use in regional projects. Please refer to SanGIS GIS data end user use agreement and disclaimer which is available at the following: http://www.sangis.org/Legal_Notice.htm. Layer does not include all recorded subdivisions maps.

attr.attrdef: For straight lines - distance along line segment. For curves - chord distance. Feet.
Central angle of curve (if appropriate). Degrees-minutes-seconds
Tangent distance for curved segments. Feet.
Length along arc for curved segments. Feet
Direction of curve direction - either left (L) or right (R) as approached from back tangent.
Unique identifier for recorded subdivsion polygon in SUBDIVISION layer that this line segment is a part of.
Type of line segment (sub-type): 1=Subdivision Boundary Line 2=Tie line 3=Other Reference Line
Direction of line segment. For curves, direction of the chord. Degrees-minutes-seconds.

overview.eaover: Subdivision boundaries are are identified by a unique Subdivision Identifier number (SubDivID). Attributes for this layer provide information recorded bearings, distances, and curves along the boundary of a subdivsion or parcel map.
